# Rule: Create Design from Figma

## Step 1: Implement Design (Static Markup & Styles)

Ask the user for the Figma link. Access it via MCP and implement the design using:

- Semantic, accessible HTML — `@accessibility.mdc`
- RSCSS structure — `@rscss.mdc`
- Typography — `_font-types.scss`
- Layout — `_ui-grid.scss`
- Buttons — `_ui-button.scss`
- No client-side JS yet

> Ask:
>
> "Is the static design implementation accurate and ready to add interactivity?"

Proceed to Step 2 if yes.

---

## Step 2: Implement Interactivity (Client-side JavaScript)

Ask the user:

> "Does this component require interactivity?"

If yes, use this boilerplate:

```
<script>
  import { BaseComponent, registerComponent } from '@/client/component.client';

  registerComponent(
    '[data-component-name]',
    class ComponentName extends BaseComponent {
      init() {
        console.log('component-name');
      }
    },
  );
</script>
```

> Replace all `component-name` / `ComponentName` / `data-component-name` with the actual component name.

If no interactivity is needed, end the workflow or guide to next steps (e.g. QA, testing, deployment).
